WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:12.137 --> 00:00:14.556 position:50% align:center
But I don't want to
live without you!

00:00:14.639 --> 00:00:16.307 position:50% align:center
Sis!

00:00:20.854 --> 00:00:23.148 position:50% align:center
It was you.

00:00:23.231 --> 00:00:25.984 position:50% align:center
--[KAREN] Alice.
--[ARASHI gasps] Karen?

00:00:34.492 --> 00:00:38.955 position:50% align:center
[KAREN]
I've failed again. How poetic.

00:00:39.039 --> 00:00:42.625 position:50% align:center
[KAREN laughs]

00:00:42.709 --> 00:00:46.046 position:50% align:center
[ARASHI gasps]
Huh?

00:00:46.129 --> 00:00:48.923 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
Kasane! Look out!

00:00:49.007 --> 00:00:51.259 position:50% align:center
[KASANE gasps]

00:00:54.387 --> 00:00:56.681 position:50% align:center
I'll hit reset as many
times as it takes.

00:00:56.765 --> 00:00:58.183 position:50% align:center
No!

00:00:58.266 --> 00:00:59.893 position:50% align:center
[ARASHI, KASANE gasp]

00:01:02.437 --> 00:01:03.646 position:50% align:center
[SHIDEN]
Wait!

00:01:07.984 --> 00:01:09.652 position:50% align:center
[HANABI]
How do we know it worked?

00:01:09.736 --> 00:01:13.698 position:50% align:center
I didn't see any data
being broadcast, did you?

00:01:13.782 --> 00:01:16.326 position:50% align:center
That's because all data
transfers are blocked in here.

00:01:16.409 --> 00:01:18.453 position:50% align:center
Oh, of course.

00:01:18.536 --> 00:01:22.123 position:50% align:center
If every citizen of New Himuka
just discovered the truth,

00:01:22.207 --> 00:01:24.834 position:50% align:center
I imagine chaos must
be breaking out.

00:01:24.918 --> 00:01:29.923 position:50% align:center
[CITIZENS chatter]

00:01:33.343 --> 00:01:34.427 position:50% align:center
[KAREN]
I don't think so.

00:01:34.511 --> 00:01:36.471 position:50% align:center
[YUITO gasps]

00:01:36.554 --> 00:01:39.808 position:50% align:center
[YUITO groans]

00:01:40.809 --> 00:01:45.814 position:50% align:center
♪

00:03:12.359 --> 00:03:13.818 position:50% align:center
[KASANE gasps]

00:03:13.902 --> 00:03:15.195 position:50% align:center
[SHIDEN]
Kasane!

00:03:18.198 --> 00:03:19.532 position:50% align:center
[SHIDEN]
Hey, take it easy.

00:03:19.616 --> 00:03:21.117 position:50% align:center
He used his Brain Eater.

00:03:21.201 --> 00:03:23.411 position:50% align:center
That'll take a huge
toll on your mind.

00:03:23.495 --> 00:03:27.290 position:50% align:center
That was odd. What do you
think he's trying to do?

00:03:27.374 --> 00:03:29.918 position:50% align:center
How did he get here?
Time travel?

00:03:30.001 --> 00:03:32.462 position:50% align:center
No. Karen just teleported.

00:03:32.545 --> 00:03:35.173 position:50% align:center
[SHIDEN] So he copied her power,
but didn't use it?

00:03:35.256 --> 00:03:36.675 position:50% align:center
I wonder if...

00:03:36.758 --> 00:03:40.387 position:50% align:center
To access Kasane's
time travel power...

00:03:40.470 --> 00:03:41.930 position:50% align:center
Yuito.

00:03:42.013 --> 00:03:43.640 position:50% align:center
...he might need you both.

00:03:43.723 --> 00:03:46.893 position:50% align:center
I'll bet right now he's trying
to steal Yuito's ability.

00:03:46.976 --> 00:03:48.478 position:50% align:center
Then we have to stop him.

00:03:48.561 --> 00:03:49.854 position:50% align:center
[ARASHI grunts]

00:03:52.273 --> 00:03:53.608 position:50% align:center
[ARAHI, SHIDEN gasps]

00:04:00.824 --> 00:04:05.245 position:50% align:center
[KASANE] I know you must be
worried about him too, Sis.

00:04:05.328 --> 00:04:09.791 position:50% align:center
I'm sorry that I wasn't
able to save you.

00:04:09.874 --> 00:04:13.545 position:50% align:center
Thank you for protecting
me until the very end.

00:04:16.131 --> 00:04:19.134 position:50% align:center
[YUITO yells]

00:04:19.217 --> 00:04:20.427 position:50% align:center
[LUKA]
Yuito!

00:04:24.597 --> 00:04:26.391 position:50% align:center
[YUITO gasps]

00:04:26.474 --> 00:04:28.977 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA gasps]

00:04:29.060 --> 00:04:30.311 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA]
Gotcha!

00:04:32.188 --> 00:04:33.398 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:04:36.526 --> 00:04:37.902 position:50% align:center
[KAREN]
You little pests.

00:04:37.986 --> 00:04:39.446 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Karen...

00:04:39.529 --> 00:04:42.157 position:50% align:center
[LUKA] Why are you trying to
copy Yuito's power, and why now?

00:04:42.240 --> 00:04:43.491 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA]
You won't win.

00:04:43.575 --> 00:04:45.952 position:50% align:center
You lost the element of
surprise a long time ago.

00:04:46.036 --> 00:04:48.121 position:50% align:center
[KAREN]
I don't need to surprise you.

00:04:48.204 --> 00:04:51.291 position:50% align:center
I could easily reduce all of you
to a smoldering pile of ash

00:04:51.374 --> 00:04:53.835 position:50% align:center
this instant, if I so desired.

00:04:53.918 --> 00:04:55.879 position:50% align:center
But if you want Yuito's power,

00:04:55.962 --> 00:04:59.090 position:50% align:center
you can't use any attack that
would damage his brain!

00:04:59.174 --> 00:05:02.969 position:50% align:center
Then how about I pulverize your
arms and legs one at a time?

00:05:03.053 --> 00:05:07.474 position:50% align:center
Or to preserve your body,
I can take your power from you.

00:05:07.557 --> 00:05:09.476 position:50% align:center
Why do you want it so badly?

00:05:09.559 --> 00:05:13.021 position:50% align:center
That is on a
need-to-know basis, boy!

00:05:14.064 --> 00:05:17.067 position:50% align:center
We're carrying out
Yakumo Sumeragi's will.

00:05:17.150 --> 00:05:20.403 position:50% align:center
It's time for us to exact his
vengeance upon the moon.

00:05:20.487 --> 00:05:22.781 position:50% align:center
--[WOMAN A] The moon?
--[MAN A] Is he serious?

00:05:23.615 --> 00:05:25.742 position:50% align:center
[KAITO]
Even with mere civilian brains,

00:05:25.825 --> 00:05:28.286 position:50% align:center
when tens of thousands
work in tandem,

00:05:28.370 --> 00:05:31.873 position:50% align:center
their Psionics can be
expanded to a vast degree.

00:05:31.956 --> 00:05:34.209 position:50% align:center
And once all of them are
connected to such a strong

00:05:34.292 --> 00:05:35.752 position:50% align:center
psionics user,

00:05:35.835 --> 00:05:39.381 position:50% align:center
our nation's military might will
be increased exponentially!

00:05:39.464 --> 00:05:41.675 position:50% align:center
[LUKA] You can't!
They're only civilians!

00:05:41.758 --> 00:05:43.510 position:50% align:center
They won't survive it!

00:05:43.593 --> 00:05:45.762 position:50% align:center
That is none of my concern.

00:05:45.845 --> 00:05:49.766 position:50% align:center
All I need is to access their
brains for one single maneuver.

00:05:49.849 --> 00:05:51.393 position:50% align:center
Secure Arahabaki!

00:05:51.476 --> 00:05:53.687 position:50% align:center
We're being flooded
with inquiries, sir!

00:05:53.770 --> 00:05:57.273 position:50% align:center
Not just that, but the council's
demanding a word with you.

00:05:57.357 --> 00:05:58.149 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:05:58.233 --> 00:06:03.238 position:50% align:center
[ALL grunting]

00:06:25.093 --> 00:06:27.137 position:50% align:center
He's way too strong.

00:06:29.139 --> 00:06:32.017 position:50% align:center
I guess I knew that,
but how can he possess

00:06:32.100 --> 00:06:33.768 position:50% align:center
so much psionic power?

00:06:33.852 --> 00:06:37.188 position:50% align:center
Huh. You're much tougher
than I expected.

00:06:37.272 --> 00:06:40.442 position:50% align:center
You may have access to
some amazing abilities,

00:06:40.525 --> 00:06:43.069 position:50% align:center
but there's still
only one of you!

00:06:43.153 --> 00:06:45.655 position:50% align:center
This won't go the way
you wanted, brother!

00:06:45.739 --> 00:06:47.615 position:50% align:center
You might as well
just leave now!

00:06:47.699 --> 00:06:50.285 position:50% align:center
We don't want to fight
against you anymore!

00:06:50.368 --> 00:06:53.830 position:50% align:center
Heh. Seems you really
don't understand.

00:06:53.913 --> 00:06:56.541 position:50% align:center
That's a demand only
the victors can make.

00:06:56.624 --> 00:06:57.834 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:06:59.461 --> 00:07:04.466 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp, groan]

00:07:07.844 --> 00:07:09.929 position:50% align:center
[YUITO groans]

00:07:10.013 --> 00:07:11.181 position:50% align:center
Wait, what did he do?

00:07:11.264 --> 00:07:12.682 position:50% align:center
I can't move at all!

00:07:12.766 --> 00:07:14.059 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA grunts]

00:07:14.142 --> 00:07:16.644 position:50% align:center
[KAREN] You never could've
won against me

00:07:16.728 --> 00:07:18.813 position:50% align:center
and definitely not in here.

00:07:18.897 --> 00:07:21.983 position:50% align:center
These cables are
connected to Arahabaki!

00:07:22.067 --> 00:07:23.818 position:50% align:center
[KAREN]
It appears I've hacked in.

00:07:23.902 --> 00:07:25.570 position:50% align:center
[LUKA]
Karen! What are you doing?

00:07:25.653 --> 00:07:30.450 position:50% align:center
[gasps, grunts]

00:07:30.533 --> 00:07:32.994 position:50% align:center
[YUITO] This feels familiar
for some reason.

00:07:36.915 --> 00:07:39.876 position:50% align:center
[YUITO] It's like when my power
resonated with Kasane's!

00:07:39.959 --> 00:07:42.045 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:07:42.128 --> 00:07:45.006 position:50% align:center
Yuito, what's wrong?

00:07:45.090 --> 00:07:50.679 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:07:50.762 --> 00:07:54.057 position:50% align:center
Oh, no. I think Karen's
gotten deep into his brain!

00:07:58.269 --> 00:08:01.106 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
It's no use! I can't stop him!

00:08:02.774 --> 00:08:05.235 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI]
Yuito's psionic power!

00:08:05.318 --> 00:08:07.612 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:08:07.696 --> 00:08:12.033 position:50% align:center
[yells]

00:08:12.117 --> 00:08:14.494 position:50% align:center
[HANABI, LUKA gasp]

00:08:17.038 --> 00:08:18.915 position:50% align:center
An earthquake? No way.

00:08:22.293 --> 00:08:23.628 position:50% align:center
Yuito.

00:08:23.795 --> 00:08:26.673 position:50% align:center
[groans]

00:08:26.756 --> 00:08:29.217 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Arahabaki's controlling my mind.

00:08:29.300 --> 00:08:31.511 position:50% align:center
What is Karen planning to do?

00:08:36.558 --> 00:08:40.937 position:50% align:center
Now then.
Let's start over, Alice.

00:08:45.817 --> 00:08:49.946 position:50% align:center
--He vanished!
--[LUKA, HANABI, TSUGUMI gasp]

00:08:50.030 --> 00:08:51.990 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA gasps]

00:08:52.615 --> 00:08:54.284 position:50% align:center
[LUKA, TSUGUMI gasp]

00:08:54.367 --> 00:08:55.577 position:50% align:center
Yuito!

00:08:56.953 --> 00:08:58.163 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA]
What happened?

00:08:58.246 --> 00:09:00.415 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI gasps]
Yuito!

00:09:00.498 --> 00:09:01.291 position:50% align:center
Say something!

00:09:01.374 --> 00:09:02.751 position:50% align:center
Yuito!

00:09:02.834 --> 00:09:04.127 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA]
Can he even hear us at all?

00:09:04.210 --> 00:09:06.421 position:50% align:center
Yuito! Yuito!

00:09:19.893 --> 00:09:25.148 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI] Alice, I understand you
protected Kasane from Togetsu.

00:09:25.231 --> 00:09:28.360 position:50% align:center
In the end, you more
than caught up with us.

00:09:32.739 --> 00:09:36.117 position:50% align:center
And now, I'll do
what must be done.

00:09:39.537 --> 00:09:41.164 position:50% align:center
[MALE OSF SOLDIER A]
It's Togetsu!

00:09:41.247 --> 00:09:43.541 position:50% align:center
Just now, they've sent
more troops!

00:09:43.625 --> 00:09:44.834 position:50% align:center
Right.

00:09:58.515 --> 00:09:59.933 position:50% align:center
What's this?

00:10:32.173 --> 00:10:33.800 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:10:41.307 --> 00:10:44.477 position:50% align:center
[gasps, screams]

00:10:44.561 --> 00:10:47.272 position:50% align:center
Yuito! It's okay,
we're right here!

00:10:47.355 --> 00:10:50.859 position:50% align:center
[KASANE gasps]
Yuito! Are we too late?

00:10:50.942 --> 00:10:52.360 position:50% align:center
Damn it!

00:10:52.444 --> 00:10:54.738 position:50% align:center
Karen showed up out of nowhere.

00:10:54.821 --> 00:10:56.489 position:50% align:center
But why only Yuito?

00:10:56.573 --> 00:10:59.701 position:50% align:center
My brother, he forced
Arahabaki to hack our minds.

00:10:59.784 --> 00:11:01.619 position:50% align:center
And then this is what happened.

00:11:01.703 --> 00:11:04.914 position:50% align:center
[YUITO screams]

00:11:04.998 --> 00:11:07.000 position:50% align:center
[HANABI]
Yuito!

00:11:07.083 --> 00:11:09.502 position:50% align:center
He's suffering from
severe brain damage.

00:11:09.586 --> 00:11:10.754 position:50% align:center
[HANABI gasps]

00:11:10.837 --> 00:11:13.840 position:50% align:center
Okay. Where's Karen right now?

00:11:13.923 --> 00:11:17.510 position:50% align:center
[LUKA] He just stole
Yuito's power and vanished.

00:11:17.594 --> 00:11:20.388 position:50% align:center
Hey... wait!

00:11:20.472 --> 00:11:23.058 position:50% align:center
No! Come back!

00:11:30.607 --> 00:11:33.151 position:50% align:center
Why'd you... leave me?

00:11:40.617 --> 00:11:42.243 position:50% align:center
Don't go...

00:11:44.788 --> 00:11:48.792 position:50% align:center
Hey wait, you guys.
Don't do this.

00:11:48.875 --> 00:11:50.335 position:50% align:center
Please don't leave.

00:11:51.961 --> 00:11:53.380 position:50% align:center
[YUITO gasps]

00:12:05.517 --> 00:12:08.311 position:50% align:center
Don't forget... them.

00:12:08.395 --> 00:12:11.189 position:50% align:center
I don't want to.

00:12:11.272 --> 00:12:13.483 position:50% align:center
But wait.

00:12:13.566 --> 00:12:15.694 position:50% align:center
Who are they again?

00:12:18.405 --> 00:12:21.199 position:50% align:center
[YUITO gasps]

00:12:21.282 --> 00:12:24.452 position:50% align:center
I can't reach him
through brain talk.

00:12:24.536 --> 00:12:25.870 position:50% align:center
I'm worried.

00:12:25.954 --> 00:12:27.247 position:50% align:center
[HANABI, LUKA gasp]

00:12:27.330 --> 00:12:29.874 position:50% align:center
I'm afraid that Yuito's memory
could be fading away

00:12:29.958 --> 00:12:30.834 position:50% align:center
by the second.

00:12:30.917 --> 00:12:32.252 position:50% align:center
[LUKA]
That's awful!

00:12:32.335 --> 00:12:34.087 position:50% align:center
[HANABI] Does that mean his
past is gonna be erased?

00:12:34.170 --> 00:12:37.924 position:50% align:center
Worse, possibly. He may
even lose his identity.

00:12:38.008 --> 00:12:40.218 position:50% align:center
But I don't wanna
think about that.

00:12:40.301 --> 00:12:42.262 position:50% align:center
[KYOKA]
Memories define a person.

00:12:42.345 --> 00:12:45.348 position:50% align:center
Once those are gone,
Yuito will be gone, as well.

00:12:45.432 --> 00:12:46.766 position:50% align:center
[HANABI]
What can we do?

00:12:46.850 --> 00:12:49.477 position:50% align:center
[KAGERO] There has to be
some kind of solution here!

00:12:49.561 --> 00:12:52.605 position:50% align:center
[HANABI]
Come on guys, let's think!

00:12:52.689 --> 00:12:55.734 position:50% align:center
What if we all copied our
memories over to Yuito?

00:12:55.817 --> 00:12:57.610 position:50% align:center
Are you seriously suggesting--?

00:12:57.694 --> 00:12:59.446 position:50% align:center
We could try it.

00:12:59.529 --> 00:13:02.365 position:50% align:center
We'll reload his connection
with our own memories.

00:13:02.449 --> 00:13:05.118 position:50% align:center
Reload it? What's that mean?

00:13:05.201 --> 00:13:09.080 position:50% align:center
We would digitize our memory
data and then send it to him

00:13:09.164 --> 00:13:10.540 position:50% align:center
using SAS.

00:13:10.623 --> 00:13:12.125 position:50% align:center
No way, that's insane!

00:13:12.208 --> 00:13:14.711 position:50% align:center
We're talking about memories,
not photo albums!

00:13:14.794 --> 00:13:16.463 position:50% align:center
Are you sure about this?

00:13:16.546 --> 00:13:18.131 position:50% align:center
Well, it is risky.

00:13:18.214 --> 00:13:21.885 position:50% align:center
We have no choice.
We need to anchor his existence.

00:13:21.968 --> 00:13:23.720 position:50% align:center
Do you think it'll work?

00:13:23.803 --> 00:13:25.096 position:50% align:center
From the research I've read,

00:13:25.180 --> 00:13:28.016 position:50% align:center
science deemed it
theoretically impossible.

00:13:28.099 --> 00:13:30.226 position:50% align:center
Quick. Fill me in anyway.

00:13:30.310 --> 00:13:32.395 position:50% align:center
I'll cobble together
the program we need.

00:13:32.479 --> 00:13:35.523 position:50% align:center
Wait a second. You mean
we're doing it right now?

00:13:43.698 --> 00:13:45.075 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Huh?

00:13:50.330 --> 00:13:51.873 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:14:11.518 --> 00:14:13.019 position:50% align:center
That's just...

00:14:13.103 --> 00:14:15.271 position:50% align:center
I'm a super-genius, remember?

00:14:17.899 --> 00:14:19.567 position:50% align:center
[ARASHI] There might still
be problems with it--

00:14:19.651 --> 00:14:21.319 position:50% align:center
We'll deal with whatever
comes our way!

00:14:21.403 --> 00:14:24.698 position:50% align:center
If it's to save Yuito,
we have to!

00:14:24.781 --> 00:14:26.533 position:50% align:center
The stakes are
pretty high, aren't they?

00:14:26.616 --> 00:14:30.078 position:50% align:center
That's alright. I enjoy a
good challenge now and then.

00:14:30.161 --> 00:14:32.831 position:50% align:center
Hanabi, you should keep
talking to Yuito.

00:14:32.914 --> 00:14:35.291 position:50% align:center
External stimuli might help
delay his memory loss

00:14:35.375 --> 00:14:37.210 position:50% align:center
a bit while we work.

00:14:37.293 --> 00:14:38.086 position:50% align:center
Right!

00:14:38.169 --> 00:14:41.840 position:50% align:center
Yuito? Hey! Can you hear me?

00:14:41.923 --> 00:14:44.759 position:50% align:center
Bingo! The program's
all coded now!

00:14:44.843 --> 00:14:45.635 position:50% align:center
Already?

00:14:45.719 --> 00:14:47.262 position:50% align:center
May I take a look?

00:14:47.345 --> 00:14:49.597 position:50% align:center
Sure. Tell me what you think.

00:14:51.099 --> 00:14:52.600 position:50% align:center
It's a partial fix.

00:14:52.684 --> 00:14:54.811 position:50% align:center
But after we stream it,
there are other steps.

00:14:54.894 --> 00:14:57.981 position:50% align:center
Recheck, rebuild,
and then the embedding.

00:14:58.064 --> 00:15:00.275 position:50% align:center
We can't afford to
make any mistakes.

00:15:00.358 --> 00:15:01.484 position:50% align:center
Yeah, you're right.

00:15:01.568 --> 00:15:03.778 position:50% align:center
Nice catch, I didn't
think about it that way.

00:15:03.862 --> 00:15:07.323 position:50% align:center
Well, the biggest issue is
Yuito's brain structure.

00:15:07.407 --> 00:15:10.076 position:50% align:center
We have to select the
right memory areas.

00:15:10.160 --> 00:15:11.244 position:50% align:center
[ARASHI]
Hm...

00:15:11.327 --> 00:15:13.663 position:50% align:center
Thankfully, I have the
perfect solution.

00:15:13.747 --> 00:15:15.957 position:50% align:center
Yuito's brain scan data.

00:15:16.041 --> 00:15:19.252 position:50% align:center
I had a feeling it would
come in handy sometime.

00:15:19.336 --> 00:15:21.379 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI]
Why do you have that on you?

00:15:21.463 --> 00:15:22.964 position:50% align:center
Back in Togetsu,

00:15:23.048 --> 00:15:26.259 position:50% align:center
you guys kept accessing those
data terminals, remember?

00:15:26.343 --> 00:15:28.511 position:50% align:center
Well, funny story, they were
stealing your information

00:15:28.595 --> 00:15:29.679 position:50% align:center
